    <prj:ScienceGoal>
        <prj:name>Probing the z=2.4 protocluster environment around SMG COSBO-29</prj:name>
        <prj:note>This is a science goal to map the 12CO (3-2) emission lines from spectroscopically confirmed members of a z=2.44 protocluster, and at the same time sampling 95 putative members with concordant photoz, in addition to COSBO-29, a possible high-redshift SMG with strong 1.2mm continuum flux. 

We plan 5 pointings in Band 3, sampling approximately 0.5 cubic Mpc and covering the cluster core and 7 spectroscopically confirmed proto-cluster members, 95 photo-z candidates, and the SMG. We consider the cold gas within these star-forming galaxies to be point-sources at this redshift.

The correlator is set up in FDM mode for all basebands in both sidebands, with the lower sideband centred automatically on the CO (3-2) line. The remaining three are similarly configured, and provide continuum measurement.

</prj:note>
