    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>We propose 2.55-hour ALMA Band 3 observations of a spectroscopically-confirmed z$\sim$2.5 protocluster in the zCOSMOS field to determine the nature of star formation in a yet-to-virialise structure that is likely to be the precursor to a modern-day massive galaxy cluster. By mapping CO(3-2) line emission over the redshift range of the spectrally confirmed targets, and exploiting the bandwidth of the ALMA channels, we are able to target 103 optically-selected extended sources, with concordant photometric redshifts, over a volume of 0.5 cubic megaparsecs. One additional target, close to the overdensity of spectroscopic galaxies, includes COSBO-29: a 1.2mm continuum detected SMG with redshift data compatible with the cluster members and possible VLA/{\it XMM-Newton} counterparts . In addition to line mapping, we will measure continuum flux at 3mm in order to both better constrain the power law index of the SMG SED, and improve photometric redshift estimates for the detected sources.</prp:abstract>
